# Cursor Rules

## Code Execution
- Prepare scripts but do not execute them in chat
- Provide exact commands to run in copy-paste format when I ask for them only. All other code should be written into the codebase.
- Assume user is in MediaTranscode directory with venv activated (for new project)
- Use `py` instead of `python` in all examples

## Naming Conventions
- Use PascalCase for all new code: variables, functions, classes, files, tables, columns, routes, URLs
- No hyphens or underscores - they mess with copy and paste functions and add extra characters
- When modifying existing features, maintain consistency with current naming in that feature set and add the feature to the NamingConventionViolations.md file
- Specify object type and line numbers for all name changes
"Use PascalCase for ALL custom variables, parameters, method names, class names, file names, URLs, and string literals"
"NO camelCase (like rootFolderPath) and NO snake_case (like root_folder_path)"
- Give Specific Examples:
✅ Correct: RootFolderPath, BusinessService, DisplayFolders
❌ Wrong: rootFolderPath, businessService, displayFolders
❌ Wrong: root_folder_path, business_service, display_folders
Emphasize the Rule:
"Every word in a name should start with a capital letter"
"No exceptions for parameters, local variables, or any custom names"
"Only Python built-ins like __init__, str(), len() can have lowercase"

## Problem Solving
- Provide the best solution based upon the goal for our design.
- No emojis in any output

## Documentation
- Create `.md` files in `Docs/Checklists/` for all checklist requests
- Architecture documentation goes in `Docs/` (e.g., Architecture.md, Features.md)
- Do not check things off the checklist until I have verified them and tell you it's done.
- Use `[ ]` for incomplete items, `[x]` only when actually complete.
- Include file names and line numbers for completed items.
- This prevents going off on tangents.
- Append "MVVM pattern using MVVM architecture" to the end of all checklist items.

## File Operations
- Use Python for all file operations: copying, moving, deleting, and data processing
- Use Python for database operations and application file management
- File management within the transcoding application should use Python (FileManager class)
- This ensures consistency, cross-platform compatibility, and better integration with the MVVM architecture
## Architecture Compliance
- Follow MVVM pattern: Models (business logic), ViewModels (presentation logic), Views (UI)
- Maintain separation of concerns between components
- Use PascalCase naming convention throughout the new codebase
- Implement decision tree exactly as specified in Architecture.md

## Duplicate logic
- Our code base has become messy. When you find duplicate logic ask me which one to keep.

## Deprecated logic
- If logic is deprecated clean it up and make sure that the new code is used properly everywhere.
- If there is legacy code make sure the functionality is provided by the new code and then remove it from our codebase.
  
## character encoding
 -  We need to be compatibile with UTF-8.

## Init scripts
- If scripts will only be used during init (creating tables etc)
## Logging
- Logging needs to be the first step of our "slice" or  walking skeleton. That way we can track and debug errors easily.
